vectorData.altText: 31. What is the cutaneous distribution of the lateral cutaneous nerve of the thigh?
That's right! The lateral cutaneous nerve of the thigh monitors the skin of the lateral thigh (D).
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

As you know, peripheral nerves carry sensory fibres as well as motor fibres. Each of them has a region of skin for which they are responsible. 
From the lumbar plexus:
The femoral nerve monitors the skin of the anterior thigh.
The obturator nerve monitors skin of the medial thigh.
The lateral cutaneous nerve of the thigh monitors the skin of the lateral thigh.
From the sacral plexus:
The posterior cutaneous nerve of the thigh monitors the skin of the posterior thigh.
